{
    "id": 23240,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - June 30, 2014",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 862.536,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 862.536,
                "byte_start": 106496,
                "byte_stop": 3556540,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 6.081,
                        "byte_start": 106496,
                        "byte_stop": 130842,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.081,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 130842,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has the opinion of the Court in our remaining two cases this morning."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 6.081,
                        "stop": 862.536,
                        "byte_start": 130842,
                        "byte_stop": 3556540,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 6.081,
                                "stop": 11.213,
                                "byte_start": 130842,
                                "byte_stop": 151427,
                                "text": "The first case is Harris v. Quinn No. 11-681."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.213,
                                "stop": 19.899,
                                "byte_start": 151427,
                                "byte_stop": 186117,
                                "text": "This case concerns the First Amendment rights of individuals who were called personal assistants under an Illinois Medicaid Program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.899,
                                "stop": 29.776,
                                "byte_start": 186117,
                                "byte_stop": 225614,
                                "text": "Specifically, the issue is whether the State of Illinois can force these personal assistants to pay money to a labor union that they do not wish to support."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.776,
                                "stop": 38.107,
                                "byte_start": 225614,
                                "byte_stop": 258947,
                                "text": "To explain how we resolved this question, I will start by explaining some of the details of this particular Illinois program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.107,
                                "stop": 51.884,
                                "byte_start": 258947,
                                "byte_stop": 314117,
                                "text": "In Illinois and throughout the country, there are many people who, due to age, illness or injury, are unable to live in their own homes without assistance and\/or unable to afford the expense of in-home care."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.884,
                                "stop": 64.529,
                                "byte_start": 314117,
                                "byte_stop": 364690,
                                "text": "In order to prevent these individuals from having to enter a nursing home or other facility, the federal Medicaid program funds state-run programs that provide in-home services to these individuals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.529,
                                "stop": 73.855,
                                "byte_start": 364690,
                                "byte_stop": 401993,
                                "text": "Forty-eight states have established such programs and one of these is Illinois, which has set up what it calls the Rehabilitation Program."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.855,
                                "stop": 88.494,
                                "byte_start": 401993,
                                "byte_stop": 460507,
                                "text": "Under this program, with one exception that I will get to, the person receiving the care who is called the customer is recognized as the employer of the personal assistant, the person who is providing the in-home care."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.494,
                                "stop": 97.221,
                                "byte_start": 460507,
                                "byte_stop": 495407,
                                "text": "The Illinois regulations state explicitly that the customer \u201cshall be the employer of the personal assistant.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.221,
                                "stop": 106.094,
                                "byte_start": 495407,
                                "byte_stop": 530934,
                                "text": "A personal assistant is defined as \u201can individual employed by the customer to provide in-home care.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.094,
                                "stop": 117.017,
                                "byte_start": 530934,
                                "byte_stop": 574610,
                                "text": "Another regulation says that the State \u201cshall not have control or input in the employment relationship between the customer and the personal assistant.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.017,
                                "stop": 123.064,
                                "byte_start": 574610,
                                "byte_stop": 598852,
                                "text": "Because of this setup, the customer has almost complete control over the employment relationship."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.064,
                                "stop": 124.887,
                                "byte_start": 598852,
                                "byte_stop": 606062,
                                "text": "Consider the question of hiring."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.887,
                                "stop": 130.061,
                                "byte_start": 606062,
                                "byte_stop": 626751,
                                "text": "State regulations established some very basic job qualifications."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.061,
                                "stop": 143.479,
                                "byte_start": 626751,
                                "byte_stop": 680458,
                                "text": "For example, a personal assistant must have a Social Security number, must be able to communicate with the customer and if the personal assistant is between the ages of 16 and 18, must be enrolled in -- in school."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.479,
                                "stop": 151.008,
                                "byte_start": 680458,
                                "byte_stop": 710552,
                                "text": "There are some others, but otherwise, the customers can do -- can hire almost anybody they want."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.008,
                                "stop": 162.243,
                                "byte_start": 710552,
                                "byte_stop": 755482,
                                "text": "Customers have complete control over the day-to-day supervision of personal assistants and customers also have unqualified discretion to fire their personal assistants."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.243,
                                "stop": 173.689,
                                "byte_start": 755482,
                                "byte_stop": 801353,
                                "text": "If for example a customer is unhappy because the personal assistant does not have the same taste in daytime T.V. shows, the customer can discharge the personal assistant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.689,
                                "stop": 175.135,
                                "byte_start": 801353,
                                "byte_stop": 807100,
                                "text": "What about the State\u0027s role?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 175.135,
                                "stop": 198.387,
                                "byte_start": 807100,
                                "byte_stop": 900096,
                                "text": "The State handles funding which consists of a mix of federal and state funds, the state sets the threshold of job requirements to which I referred, a state official must approve the document called a Service Plan that sets out the basic services that each customer will receive and the State assists customers in a few other ways, and that is about it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.387,
                                "stop": 211.898,
                                "byte_start": 900096,
                                "byte_stop": 954117,
                                "text": "As a result of the scheme, the Illinois State Labor Relations Board ruled that a union could not represent the personal assistants for the purpose of bargaining with the State, because the State was not the assistants\u0027 employer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.898,
                                "stop": 215.386,
                                "byte_start": 954117,
                                "byte_stop": 968119,
                                "text": "That changed in 2003 when Governor Rod Blagojevich took office."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.386,
                                "stop": 229.205,
                                "byte_start": 968119,
                                "byte_stop": 1023394,
                                "text": "Governor Blagojevich issued an executive order declaring that the personal assistants were state employees for the purpose of engaging in collective bargaining with the State."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 229.205,
                                "stop": 232.889,
                                "byte_start": 1023394,
                                "byte_stop": 1038127,
                                "text": "And the state legislature then codified that order."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 232.889,
                                "stop": 243.482,
                                "byte_start": 1038127,
                                "byte_stop": 1080445,
                                "text": "The new law deems the personal assistants to be public employees but solely for the purposes of coverage under the Illinois Public Labor Relations Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.482,
                                "stop": 245.506,
                                "byte_start": 1080445,
                                "byte_stop": 1088596,
                                "text": "That\u0027s a quote from the law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 245.506,
                                "stop": 254.271,
                                "byte_start": 1088596,
                                "byte_stop": 1123600,
                                "text": "And the legislature -- legislature was careful to specify that the personal assistants are not state employees for any other purpose."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 254.271,
                                "stop": 265.877,
                                "byte_start": 1123600,
                                "byte_stop": 1170098,
                                "text": "So, if a personal assistant commits a tort while on the job let\u0027s say a personal assistant steals from a customer or abuses the customer, the State has no liability."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 265.877,
                                "stop": 277.885,
                                "byte_start": 1170098,
                                "byte_stop": 1218058,
                                "text": "Personal assistants are also not entitled to the pension or health benefits provided for full-fledged state employees as well as a host of other benefits that are detailed in our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 277.885,
                                "stop": 287.709,
                                "byte_start": 1218058,
                                "byte_stop": 1257347,
                                "text": "As I mentioned, the new law deemed that personal assistants to be state employees solely for the purposes of coverage under the Illinois Public Labor Relations Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 287.709,
                                "stop": 292.183,
                                "byte_start": 1257347,
                                "byte_stop": 1275319,
                                "text": "And that move had important consequences that gave rise to this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 292.183,
                                "stop": 305.705,
                                "byte_start": 1275319,
                                "byte_stop": 1329340,
                                "text": "It meant that the personal assistants could unionize and it also meant that those personal assistants who do not want to join the union or support its work may be forced to pay what is known as an agency fee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 305.705,
                                "stop": 319.67,
                                "byte_start": 1329340,
                                "byte_stop": 1385242,
                                "text": "This means that these objecting non-members must pay the union dues -- must pay the union dues minus the portion of those dues that the union would use for political or ideological purposes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 319.67,
                                "stop": 328.743,
                                "byte_start": 1385242,
                                "byte_stop": 1421500,
                                "text": "After the enactment of the new law, the local chapter of the Service Employees International Union was recognized as the personal assistants union."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 328.743,
                                "stop": 336.002,
                                "byte_start": 1421500,
                                "byte_stop": 1450548,
                                "text": "The union and the State entered into a collective bargaining agreement requiring non-members to pay an agency fee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 336.002,
                                "stop": 345.97,
                                "byte_start": 1450548,
                                "byte_stop": 1490463,
                                "text": "And the number of personal assistants who do not want to subsidize the union then brought the suit claiming that the agency fee violates their First Amendment rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 345.97,
                                "stop": 357.735,
                                "byte_start": 1490463,
                                "byte_stop": 1537484,
                                "text": "Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit rejected that challenge based on the case that this Court decided in 1977 called Abood v. Detroit Board of Education."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 357.735,
                                "stop": 375.378,
                                "byte_start": 1537484,
                                "byte_stop": 1608014,
                                "text": "In Abood, this Court held that the First Amendment permitted the Detroit Board of Education to demand that all public school teachers pay an agency fee to a union regardless of whether they were members or wish to support the union\u0027s agenda."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 375.378,
                                "stop": 379.533,
                                "byte_start": 1608014,
                                "byte_stop": 1624733,
                                "text": "Abood reasoned that this was permissible for two reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 379.533,
                                "stop": 389.364,
                                "byte_start": 1624733,
                                "byte_stop": 1664021,
                                "text": "First, to preserve what is called labor peace, which chiefly means preventing rivalries between competing unions and conflicting demands by such unions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 389.364,
                                "stop": 399.798,
                                "byte_start": 1664021,
                                "byte_stop": 1705712,
                                "text": "Second, to prevent free riding that is workers benefiting from a union\u0027s efforts without paying a share to the union\u0027s expenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 399.798,
                                "stop": 407.265,
                                "byte_start": 1705712,
                                "byte_stop": 1735596,
                                "text": "Two terms ago, in the case called Knox v. SEIU, we noted that Abood is something of anomaly."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 407.265,
                                "stop": 408.375,
                                "byte_start": 1735596,
                                "byte_stop": 1740089,
                                "text": "Why is that so?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 408.375,
                                "stop": 412.898,
                                "byte_start": 1740089,
                                "byte_stop": 1758166,
                                "text": "To understand, it\u0027s necessary to go back to some basic principles."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 412.898,
                                "stop": 419.236,
                                "byte_start": 1758166,
                                "byte_stop": 1783453,
                                "text": "The First Amendment obviously prevents the government from suppressing speech on important public issues."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 419.236,
                                "stop": 426.463,
                                "byte_start": 1783453,
                                "byte_stop": 1812396,
                                "text": "Let\u0027s say someone wants to give a speech in a public park and wants to say that the local school board is spending too much money."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 426.463,
                                "stop": 434.566,
                                "byte_start": 1812396,
                                "byte_stop": 1844788,
                                "text": "The local authorities cannot prohibit that speech for the purpose of preventing the expression of a view with which they disagree."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 434.566,
                                "stop": 449.222,
                                "byte_start": 1844788,
                                "byte_stop": 1903407,
                                "text": "And by the same token, the local authorities could not require all parents in the town to pay dues to a private group that distributes leaflets or runs newspaper ads supporting increase spending for schools."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 449.222,
                                "stop": 464.25,
                                "byte_start": 1903407,
                                "byte_stop": 1963593,
                                "text": "Even though some might say that all parents benefit from the efforts of this group and therefore might be called free riders, we have never held that the First Amendment permits anything like this except in Abood."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 464.25,
                                "stop": 473.595,
                                "byte_start": 1963593,
                                "byte_stop": 2000896,
                                "text": "So our opinion in this case examines the curious way in which the anomalies holding in Abood entered our First Amendment jurisprudence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 473.595,
                                "stop": 479.427,
                                "byte_start": 2000896,
                                "byte_stop": 2024302,
                                "text": "We also explained that Abood\u0027s reasoning is questionable for a number of reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 479.427,
                                "stop": 481.804,
                                "byte_start": 2024302,
                                "byte_stop": 2033810,
                                "text": "Among other things we note the following."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 481.804,
                                "stop": 503.139,
                                "byte_start": 2033810,
                                "byte_stop": 2119074,
                                "text": "Abood failed to appreciate the difference between the core union speech involuntarily subsidized by dissenting public-sector employees and the core union speech involuntarily funded by their counterparts in the private-sector who were not protected by the First Amendment, because private sector employers are not state actors."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 503.139,
                                "stop": 518.094,
                                "byte_start": 2119074,
                                "byte_stop": 2178947,
                                "text": "Abood failed to appreciate the conceptual difficulty of distinguishing in public-sector cases between union expenditures that are made for collective bargaining purposes and those that are made for political ends."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 518.094,
                                "stop": 531.551,
                                "byte_start": 2178947,
                                "byte_stop": 2232759,
                                "text": "Abood does not seem to have anticipated the magnitude of the practical problems that would result from attempting to classify public-sector union expenditures as falling into one or the other of these two categories."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 531.551,
                                "stop": 543.035,
                                "byte_start": 2232759,
                                "byte_stop": 2278734,
                                "text": "Abood likewise did not foresee the practical problems that would face objecting non-members who believe that a union is using their money for political or ideological purposes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 543.035,
                                "stop": 556.202,
                                "byte_start": 2278734,
                                "byte_stop": 2331397,
                                "text": "Finally, the Abood Court erroneously assumed that an agency fee provision is inextricably linked to a union status as the exclusive representative of all the employees in the relevant unit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 556.202,
                                "stop": 560.996,
                                "byte_start": 2331397,
                                "byte_stop": 2350519,
                                "text": "Despite all these, the Court of Appeals dramatically expanded Abood\u0027s reach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 560.996,
                                "stop": 572.514,
                                "byte_start": 2350519,
                                "byte_stop": 2396599,
                                "text": "Abood involved full-fledged public employees, but the personal assistants in the Rehabilitation Program are not anything like full-fledged public employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 572.514,
                                "stop": 581.066,
                                "byte_start": 2396599,
                                "byte_stop": 2430767,
                                "text": "As I have explained, for every purpose but one, a personal assistant\u0027s employer is the customer for whom the personal assistant provides care."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 581.066,
                                "stop": 587.716,
                                "byte_start": 2430767,
                                "byte_stop": 2457412,
                                "text": "And because of this, the Court\u0027s reasoning in Abood whatever its strengths or weaknesses does not apply."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 587.716,
                                "stop": 590.834,
                                "byte_start": 2457412,
                                "byte_stop": 2469846,
                                "text": "I will not go into this at length, but here is one illustration."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 590.834,
                                "stop": 602.524,
                                "byte_start": 2469846,
                                "byte_stop": 2516658,
                                "text": "In defense of Abood, it is argued that non-members of the union may be forced to pay money to the union because the union is required by labor law to provide services for them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 602.524,
                                "stop": 615.806,
                                "byte_start": 2516658,
                                "byte_stop": 2569738,
                                "text": "For example, suppose a non-member has a grievance, suppose that the non-member was demoted, disciplined or discharged, the union has a duty to represent the non-member in the same way that it would represent a union member."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 615.806,
                                "stop": 625.686,
                                "byte_start": 2569738,
                                "byte_stop": 2609340,
                                "text": "Under the Rehabilitation Program scheme however, the union cannot do this because all of those matters are within the sole discretion of a customer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 625.686,
                                "stop": 631.016,
                                "byte_start": 2609340,
                                "byte_stop": 2630656,
                                "text": "The union can handle grievances only as the matter is controlled by the State."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 631.016,
                                "stop": 640.012,
                                "byte_start": 2630656,
                                "byte_stop": 2666600,
                                "text": "For this reason and others, while we do not overrule or reaffirm Abood, we refuse to extend it to cover workers who were not full-fledged state employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 640.012,
                                "stop": 644.445,
                                "byte_start": 2666600,
                                "byte_stop": 2684364,
                                "text": "And without Abood, the agency fee in this case cannot stand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 644.445,
                                "stop": 647.765,
                                "byte_start": 2684364,
                                "byte_stop": 2697634,
                                "text": "We reject the argument that the fee promotes labor peace."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 647.765,
                                "stop": 659.17,
                                "byte_start": 2697634,
                                "byte_stop": 2743192,
                                "text": "This argument is largely based on the incorrect premise that such a fee is inextricably linked to a union status as the exclusive bargaining agent for all the employees in the union."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 659.17,
                                "stop": 661.706,
                                "byte_start": 2743192,
                                "byte_stop": 2753327,
                                "text": "That is not true as federal law shows."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 661.706,
                                "stop": 675.995,
                                "byte_start": 2753327,
                                "byte_stop": 2810483,
                                "text": "The unions serve as the exclusive bargaining agent for all the employees and some components of the Federal Government, but employees in those units may not under federal statutory law be forced to pay an agency fee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 675.995,
                                "stop": 689.081,
                                "byte_start": 2810483,
                                "byte_stop": 2862832,
                                "text": "We also reject the argument that without the extra money obtained as a result of the agency fee provision, the union in this case could not effectively asked the State of increase the personal assistants\u0027 wages and benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 689.081,
                                "stop": 693.094,
                                "byte_start": 2862832,
                                "byte_stop": 2878924,
                                "text": "There is no support for that argument."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 693.094,
                                "stop": 703.875,
                                "byte_start": 2878924,
                                "byte_stop": 2922078,
                                "text": "Attempting to find a new basis to sustain the Illinois scheme, the Federal Government and the dissent argued that this case should be governed by our decision in Pickering v. Board of Education."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 703.875,
                                "stop": 717.66,
                                "byte_start": 2922078,
                                "byte_stop": 2977144,
                                "text": "Pickering in subsequent cases in that line concerns situations in which a public employee suffers some sort of adverse employment action because the employee spoke out in a way that the public employer did not -- did not like."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 717.66,
                                "stop": 726.867,
                                "byte_start": 2977144,
                                "byte_stop": 3014029,
                                "text": "In situations like that, we have held the employee has First Amendment protection so long as the employee\u0027s speech is on a matter of public concern."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 726.867,
                                "stop": 739.42,
                                "byte_start": 3014029,
                                "byte_stop": 3064184,
                                "text": "In this case, the Federal Government and the dissent argued that the speech at issue here, for example, speech by a union in favor of increased Medicaid spending is not a matter of public concern."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 739.42,
                                "stop": 741.963,
                                "byte_start": 3064184,
                                "byte_stop": 3074424,
                                "text": "That argument flies in the face of reality."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 741.963,
                                "stop": 749.06,
                                "byte_start": 3074424,
                                "byte_stop": 3102741,
                                "text": "In recent years, Medicaid expenditures have represented nearly a quarter of all State expenditures."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 749.06,
                                "stop": 755.706,
                                "byte_start": 3102741,
                                "byte_stop": 3129386,
                                "text": "Medicaid spending and government spending in general are matters of great public concern."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 755.706,
                                "stop": 765.673,
                                "byte_start": 3129386,
                                "byte_stop": 3169196,
                                "text": "Here is what is at stake in this case, compelling a person to mouth words that are contrary to the person\u0027s beliefs is an affront to personal dignity."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 765.673,
                                "stop": 774.187,
                                "byte_start": 3169196,
                                "byte_stop": 3203260,
                                "text": "It undermines the free marketplace of ideas on which our democratic form of government is based and it violates the First Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 774.187,
                                "stop": 783.63,
                                "byte_start": 3203260,
                                "byte_stop": 3241085,
                                "text": "The same is true when the government demands that a person subsidize another private individual or group that delivers the same objectionable message."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 783.63,
                                "stop": 790.881,
                                "byte_start": 3241085,
                                "byte_stop": 3270029,
                                "text": "Think of some private group that spends a lot of money propagating ideas that you strongly dislike."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 790.881,
                                "stop": 800.881,
                                "byte_start": 3270029,
                                "byte_stop": 3310049,
                                "text": "Now, ask yourself how you would feel if the Federal Government or the government of your State forced you to contribute to that group and to pay for speech that you deplore."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 800.881,
                                "stop": 805.732,
                                "byte_start": 3310049,
                                "byte_stop": 3329484,
                                "text": "Abood allowed full-fledged public employees to be put in this position."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 805.732,
                                "stop": 815.767,
                                "byte_start": 3329484,
                                "byte_stop": 3369608,
                                "text": "But in this case, Illinois and the Federal Government would have us permit the same thing for personal assistants who were nothing like full-fledged public employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 815.767,
                                "stop": 824.345,
                                "byte_start": 3369608,
                                "byte_stop": 3403880,
                                "text": "Allowing Abood to apply outside the confines of full-fledged public employment would present a grave threat to First Amendment rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 824.345,
                                "stop": 831.47,
                                "byte_start": 3403880,
                                "byte_stop": 3432406,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals erred in extending Abood -- Abood beyond the confines of real public employees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 831.47,
                                "stop": 844.432,
                                "byte_start": 3432406,
                                "byte_stop": 3484233,
                                "text": "However, we agree with the Court of Appeals that the claims of those petitioners who work not in the Rehabilitation Program but in another program called the Disabilities Program are not right."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 844.432,
                                "stop": 854.593,
                                "byte_start": 3484233,
                                "byte_stop": 3524880,
                                "text": "For these reasons, the judgment of the Court of Appeals is reversed in part and affirmed in part and the case is remanded for further proceedings consistent with this opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 854.593,
                                "stop": 862.536,
                                "byte_start": 3524880,
                                "byte_stop": 3556540,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Ginsburg, Breyer and Sotomayor have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
